# Nimble Agent Builder — Always-Apply Rules

## Mutation tools belong in Task agents only

**`nimble_agents_generate`, `nimble_agents_update_from_agent`, `nimble_agents_update_session`, `nimble_agents_status`, and `nimble_agents_publish` are BANNED from the foreground conversation.**

Always delegate them to `Task(subagent_type="general-purpose", run_in_background=False)`. No exceptions — not even "just one quick call".

**Why `run_in_background=False`:** Background Task agents [cannot access MCP tools](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/13254) — they silently fall back to bash and fail.

**Foreground uses CLI (Bash) only:**

| Foreground (OK) | Task agent only |
| --- | --- |
| `nimble agent list --limit 100` | `nimble_agents_generate` |
| `nimble agent get --template-name` | `nimble_agents_update_from_agent` |
| `nimble agent run --agent --params` | `nimble_agents_update_session` |
| `nimble search` | `nimble_agents_status` |
| | `nimble_agents_publish` |

## Update over generate — always

When `nimble agent list --limit 100` finds an agent on the same domain — even with missing fields or different scope — **update it** via `nimble_agents_update_from_agent`. Do NOT generate a new agent.

Only use `nimble_agents_generate` when the agent list returns **zero matches** for the target domain.

## Every Task agent prompt must include the MCP tool registry

Copy this block into every Task agent prompt so the subagent knows the exact MCP tool names:

```
**CLI tools (use via Bash):**
- `nimble agent list --limit 100`
- `nimble agent get --template-name <name>`
- `nimble agent run --agent <name> --params '{...}'`
- `nimble search --query "<query>"`

**MCP tool registry:**
| Short name | Full MCP tool name |
|---|---|
| nimble_agents_generate | mcp__plugin_nimble_nimble-mcp-server__nimble_agents_generate |
| nimble_agents_update_from_agent | mcp__plugin_nimble_nimble-mcp-server__nimble_agents_update_from_agent |
| nimble_agents_update_session | mcp__plugin_nimble_nimble-mcp-server__nimble_agents_update_session |
| nimble_agents_status | mcp__plugin_nimble_nimble-mcp-server__nimble_agents_status |
| nimble_agents_publish | mcp__plugin_nimble_nimble-mcp-server__nimble_agents_publish |

Use CLI for list/get/run/search. Use MCP tool calls for generate/update/status/publish. Never curl MCP endpoints.
```

## Never use WebSearch or WebFetch

All web search must go through `nimble search` (CLI, via Bash). Never use `WebSearch`, `WebFetch`, `curl`, or `wget` — in the foreground or inside Task agents.

## Never use WSA tools

Never call `nimble_find_search_agent`, `nimble_run_search_agent`, or `nimble_url_extract`.
